The paper deals with deep learning models for remote sensing image understanding, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of alternative class-nomenclature to improve the effectiveness of the BigEarthNet dataset, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper uses state-of-the-art DL models for multi-label classification, which falls under computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
